y%20around%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F3%2F12%2Fwhy-is-indias-citizenship-amendment-act-so-controversial%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECitizenship%20Amendment%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20renewed%20in%20India%20Monday%20as%20the%20government%20announced%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20law%20passed%20in%202019%20that%20opens%20a%20new%20path%20to%20citizenship%20for%20past%20arrivals%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan.%20The%20act%20has%20been%20deemed%20anti-Muslim%20as%20it%20only%20applies%20to%20Hindu%2C%20Parsi%2C%20Sikh%2C%20Buddhist%2C%20Jain%20and%20Christian%20refugees%20from%20the%20three%20Muslim-majority%20countries%2C%20but%20leaves%20out%20Muslim%20refugees.%20It%20also%20does%20not%20take%20into%20account%20non-Muslim%20refugees%20from%20non-Muslim%20countries%20and%20only%20applies%20to%20those%20who%20arrived%20in%202014%20or%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtests%20against%20the%20act%20had%20turned%20violent%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F20473%2Fstates-with-the-highest-number-of-districts-recording-violent-incidents-police-action-deaths-during-caa-protests%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20and%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20flared%20up%20again%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20including%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fprotests-erupt-across-india-against-caa-implementation-see-pics-2934333%237%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20cities%2C%20in%20Kerala%20and%20in%20Assam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Northern%20region%20that%20hosts%20the%20most%20Muslims.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fopposition-ruled-kerala-bengal-say-no-to-caa-after-centre-notifies-rules-2513530-2024-03-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpposition-led%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Kerala%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0announced%20that%20they%20would%20not%20be%20implementing%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20its%20passage%20in%202019%2C%20the%20act%20was%20looking%20to%20cut%20the%20wait%20time%20to%20acquire%20citizenship%20for%20those%20included%20down%20to%20a%20minimum%20of%20five%20years.%20Now%2C%202014%20arrivals%20are%20already%20quite%20close%20to%20the%20regular%2011-year%20cutoff%20for%20the%20naturalization%20of%20foreigners%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20the%20act%20includes%20another%20crucial%20exemption%20for%20the%20covered%20groups%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20apply%20for%20citizenship%20even%20without%20being%20able%20to%20prove%20legal%20residence%20since%20arrival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Frefugee-statistics%2Fdownload%2F%3Furl%3D01xW3x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20the%20UNHCR%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20law%20is%20in%20fact%20ignoring%20the%20largest%20refugee%20groups%20in%20India%20and%20if%20it%20is%20aiding%20the%20included%20groups%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20those%20without%20documentation.%20Only%2012%20refugees%20from%20Bangladesh%20and%20none%20from%20Pakistan%20were%20registered%20in%20India%20with%20the%20official%20agency%20as%20of%20mid-2023.%20The%20largest%20groups%20of%20refugees%20and%20asylum-seekers%20in%20the%20country%20come%20from%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20the%20Muslim%20minority%20of%20Rohingyas%20in%20Myanmar%20and%20from%20China%2C%20specifically%20Tibet.%20Afghanistan%20is%20the%20exception%20with%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20registered%20refugees%20and%20asylum-seekers%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20however%2C%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20affecting%20all%20population%20groups%20in%20the%20country%2C%20these%20could%20be%20either%20Muslims%20(including%20of%20the%20persecuted%20Hazara%20ethnic%20group)%20or%20members%20of%20the%20smaller%20Hindu%2C%20Sikh%2C%20Parsi%20and%20potentially%20Christian%20minorities%20of%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcensusindia.gov.in%2Fcensus.website%2Fdata%2Fcensus-tables%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Census%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0shows%20that%20immigration%20waves%20from%20Pakistan%20as%20well%20as%20Bangladesh%20happened%20before%201991%2C%20when%20almost%2080%20percent%20of%20those%20who%20were%20born%20in%20Pakistan%20or%20Bangladesh%20and%20lived%20in%20India%20in%202011%20immigrated.%20Between%202002%20and%202011%2C%20only%206.5-7.5%20percent%20of%20all%20immigrants%20from%20these%20two%20countries%20arrived%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%20India%20Sees%20Relatively%20Few%20Refugees%20from%20CAA%20Countries%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F31902%2Frefugee-asylum-seeker-populations-in-india-from-most-common-countries-and-caa-countries-of-origin%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%20India%20Sees%20Relatively%20Few%20Refugees%20from%20CAA%20Countries%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.statcdn.com%2FInfographic%2Fimages%2Fnormal%2F31902.jpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EYou%20will%20find%20more%20infographics%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchartoftheday%2F%5C%22%3EStatista%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20this%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F31902%2Frefugee-asylum-seeker-populations-in-india-from-most-common-countries-and-caa-countries-of-origin%2F%3Futm_source%3DStatista%2BNewsletters%26utm_campaign%3D8152a2dd13-India_DailyData_Th_KW11_2024%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_term%3D0_-b5df2ccfad-%255BLIST_EMAIL_ID%255D%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710390649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F07121932%2FUntitled-design-2021-12-07T121919.360.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchart-india-sees-relatively-few-refugees-from-caa-countries%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Only%2012%20refugees%20from%20Bangladesh%20and%20none%20from%20Pakistan%20were%20registered%20in%20India%20with%20the%20official%20agency%20as%20of%20mid-2023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchart-india-sees-relatively-few-refugees-from-caa-countries%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BCitizenship%20Law%20CAA%20Will%20Never%20Be%20Taken%20Back%2C%26quot%3B%20Asserts%20Amit%20Shah%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDays%20after%20the%20Centre%20notified%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20law%20will%20never%20be%20taken%20back%20and%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20will%20never%20compromise%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20our%20sovereign%20right%20to%20ensure%20Indian%20citizenship%20in%20our%20country.%20We%20will%20never%20compromise%20on%20it%20and%20CAA%20will%20never%20be%20taken%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20Opposition%20bloc%20INDIA%2C%20specifically%20a%20Congress%20leader%20saying%20that%20they%20would%20repeal%20the%20law%20when%20they%20come%20to%20power%2C%20the%20Home%20Minister%20said%20that%20even%20the%20Opposition%20is%20aware%20it%20has%20bleak%20chances%20of%20coming%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20the%20INDI%20alliance%20knows%20that%20it%20will%20not%20come%20into%20power.%20CAA%20has%20been%20brought%20by%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government.%20It%20is%20impossible%20to%20repeal%20it.%20We%20will%20spread%20awareness%20about%20it%20in%20the%20whole%20nation%20so%20that%20those%20who%20want%20to%20repeal%20it%20do%20not%20get%20a%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20Minister%20dismissed%20criticism%20that%20the%20%26quot%3BCAA%20is%20unconstitutional%26quot%3B%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20does%20not%20violate%20the%20constitutional%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20always%20talk%20about%20Article%2014.%20They%20forget%20that%20there%20are%20two%20clauses%20in%20that%20Article.%20This%20law%20does%20not%20violate%20Article%2014.%20There%20is%20a%20clear%2C%20reasonable%20classification%20here.%20This%20is%20a%20law%20for%20those%20who%2C%20due%20to%20partition%2C%20remained%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Bangladesh%20and%20were%20facing%20religious%20persecution%20and%20decided%20to%20come%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Union%20Minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReplying%20to%20the%20Opposition's%20claim%20of%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20notification%20coming%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFirst%20of%20all%2C%20I%20will%20talk%20about%20the%20timing.%20All%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20including%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20are%20doing%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejhooth%20ki%20rajneeti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(politics%20of%20lies).%20So%20the%20question%20of%20timing%20does%20not%20arise.%20The%20BJP%20made%20it%20clear%20in%20its%202019%20manifesto%20that%20it%20will%20bring%20CAA%20and%20provide%20Indian%20citizenship%20to%20refugees%20(from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan).%20It%20has%20a%20clear%20agenda%20and%20under%20that%20promise%2C%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Bill%20was%20passed%20in%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20in%202019.%20It%20got%20delayed%20due%20to%20Covid.%20The%20BJP%20cleared%20its%20agenda%20well%20before%20it%20got%20its%20mandate%20in%20the%20polls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRules%20are%20now%20a%20formality.%20There%20is%20no%20question%20of%20timing%2C%20political%20gain%2C%20or%20loss.%20Now%2C%20the%20Opposition%20wants%20to%20consolidate%20their%20vote%20bank%20by%20doing%20appeasement%20politics...%20They%20have%20been%20exposed.%20CAA%20is%20the%20law%20for%20the%20entire%20country%20and%20I%20have%20reiterated%20nearly%2041%20times%20in%20four%20years%20that%20it%20will%20become%20a%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Home%20Minister%20said%20that%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20question%20of%20political%20gain%20as%20the%20BJP's%20main%20aim%20is%20to%20provide%20rights%20and%20justice%20to%20persecuted%20minorities%20coming%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Opposition%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20surgical%20strikes%20and%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20linked%20it%20with%20political%20gain.%20So%20should%20we%20not%20take%20stern%20steps%20against%20terrorism%3F%20We%20have%20been%20saying%20since%201950%20that%20we%20will%20withdraw%20Article%20370%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Home%20Minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20spoken%20on%20CAA%20at%20least%2041%20times%20on%20different%20platforms%20and%20spoken%20on%20it%20in%20detail%20that%20the%20minorities%20of%20the%20country%20need%20not%20be%20afraid%20because%20it%20has%20no%20provision%20to%20take%20back%20the%20rights%20of%20any%20citizen.%20The%20CAA%20aims%20to%20confer%20Indian%20citizenship%20to%20persecuted%20non-Muslim%20migrants%20-%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Jains%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Parsis%2C%20and%20Christians%20-%20who%20migrated%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20and%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%20Through%20this%20law%2C%20their%20sufferings%20can%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Home%20Minister%20was%20critical%20of%20opposition%20leaders%20-%20AIMIM's%20Asaddudin%20Owaisi%20and%20West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20-%20for%20claiming%20that%20the%20CAA%20was%20anti-Muslim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20cannot%20see%20this%20law%20in%20isolation.%20On%20August%2015%2C%201947%2C%20our%20country%20was%20partitioned.%20Our%20country%20was%20partitioned%20into%20three%20parts.%20Bharatiya%20Jan%20Sangh%20and%20BJP%20were%20always%20against%20the%20Partition.%20We%20never%20wanted%20India%20to%20be%20partitioned%20based%20on%20religion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20when%20the%20country%20was%20partitioned%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%2C%20minorities%20faced%20persecution.%20They%20were%20being%20converted%2C%20women%20were%20being%20tortured%2C%20and%20they%20came%20to%20India.%20They%20came%20for%20refuge.%20Don't%20they%20have%20a%20right%20to%20get%20citizenship%3F%20Even%20Congress%20leaders%20during%20the%20partition%20in%20their%20speeches%20said%20that%20the%20minorities%20should%20stay%20wherever%20they%20were%20due%20to%20the%20widespread%20bloodshed%20and%20would%20be%20welcomed%20later%20in%20our%20country.%20Now%20they%20have%20started%20vote%20bank%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Shah%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20government's%20moral%20duty%20to%20ensure%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20persecuted%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20were%20part%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%20and%20who%20were%20prosecuted%20or%20tortured%20should%20be%20given%20refuge%20in%20India%20and%20this%20is%20our%20social%20and%20Constitutional%20responsibility.%20Now%20if%20you%20look%20closely%20at%20the%20statistics%2C%20in%20Pakistan%20when%20the%20Partition%20happened%2C%20there%20were%2023%25%20Hindus%20and%20Sikhs%20but%20now%20only%203.7%25%20of%20them%20are%20left.%20Where%20did%20they%20go%3F%20They%20have%20not%20returned%20here.%20They%20were%20converted%2C%20tortured%2C%20and%20insulted.%20They%20were%20given%20second-class%20status.%20Where%20will%20they%20go%3F%20Will%20the%20country%2C%20Parliament%2C%20and%20the%20political%20parties%20not%20think%20about%20them%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20Home%20Minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20Afghanistan%2C%20at%20the%20moment%20there%20are%20now%20only%20about%20500%20Hindus...%20don't%20they%20have%20the%20right%20to%20live%20as%20per%20their%20beliefs%3F%20When%20Bharat%20was%20one%2C%20they%20were%20our%20brothers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESlamming%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20for%20his%20remarks%20that%20CAA%20will%20take%20away%20jobs%20meant%20for%20India's%20youth%2C%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20crime%2C%20the%20Union%20Minister%20said%20that%20people%20who%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20law%20are%20already%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20are%20so%20concerned%20why%20are%20they%20not%20talking%20about%20Bangladeshi%20infiltrators%20and%20Rohingyas%3F%20Because%20they%20are%20doing%20vote%20bank%20politics.%20Delhi%20elections%20are%20tough%20for%20them.%20That's%20why%20they%20are%20indulging%20in%20vote%20bank%20politics%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmit%20Shah%20also%20questioned%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20for%20alleging%20that%20citizenship%20of%20minorities%20would%20be%20taken%20away%20due%20to%20the%20CAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20requesting%20Mamata%20ji%2C%20that%20there%20are%20several%20platforms%20to%20do%20politics.%20Please%20don't%20harm%20Bengali%20Hindus%20from%20Bangladesh.%20I%20challenge%20her%20publicly%20to%20show%20one%20clause%20that%20has%20the%20provision%20of%20taking%20away%20citizenship%20of%20any%20Indian.%20Her%20intention%20is%20to%20create%20differences%20between%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20to%20consolidate%20vote%20bank.%20The%20CAA%20must%20be%20implemented.%20If%20she%20wants%20to%20do%20anything%2C%20she%20should%20stop%20infiltration.%20But%20she%20is%20not%20cooperating%2C%26quot%3B%20Amit%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2011%2C%20the%20Union%20Home%20Ministry%20notified%20rules%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%2C%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20passed%20by%20Parliament%20in%202019%2C%20aims%20to%20confer%20Indian%20citizenship%20to%20persecuted%20non-Muslim%20migrants%20-%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Jains%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Parsis%2C%20and%20Christians%20-%20who%20migrated%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20and%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710390600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Ft2bjcimg_amit-shah_650x400_14_March_24.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizenship-law-caa-will-never-be-taken-back-asserts-amit-shah-5235098%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Days%20after%20the%20Centre%20notified%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20law%20will%20never%20be%20taken%20back%20and%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20will%20never%20compromise%20with%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizenship-law-caa-will-never-be-taken-back-asserts-amit-shah-5235098%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizenship-law-caa-will-never-be-taken-back-asserts-amit-shah-5235098%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizenship-law-caa-will-never-be-taken-back-asserts-amit-shah-5235098%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20devastating%20fried%20chicken%20shop%20explosion%20in%20China%20has%20killed%207%20people%2