rl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Lord%20of%20the%20Flutes'%3A%20Archaeologists%20in%20Panama%20find%20ancient%20tomb%20filled%20with%20gold%20treasure%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710390022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108481231%2Cimgsize-1028218.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Flord-of-the-flutes-archaeologists-in-panama-find-ancient-tomb-filled-with-gold-treasure%2Farticleshow%2F108480777.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108480777.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20recent%20discovery%20at%20El%20Ca%C3%B1o%20Archaeological%20Park%20in%20Panama%20of%20a%20religious%20leader's%20grave%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BLord%20of%20the%20Flutes%2C%26quot%3B%20containing%20golden%20artifacts%20and%20sacrificial%20victims%2C%20sheds%20light%20on%20ancient%20civilizations%20in%20Panama%20and%20their%20societal%20practices.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Flord-of-the-flutes-archaeologists-in-panama-find-ancient-tomb-filled-with-gold-treasure%2Farticleshow%2F108480777.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Flord-of-the-flutes-archaeologists-in-panama-find-ancient-tomb-filled-with-gold-treasure%2Famp_articleshow%2F108480777.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Flord-of-the-flutes-archaeologists-in-panama-find-ancient-tomb-filled-with-gold-treasure%2Famp_articleshow%2F108480777.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hapur%20Mob%20Lynching%20Conviction%3A%20Court%20Finds%20UP%20Police%20Guilty%20of%20Negligence%20in%20Investigation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F23102651%2Fhapur_twitter1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20court%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20while%20sentencing%2010%20Hindu%20men%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20for%20lynching%20a%20Muslim%20goat%20trader%20in%20Hapur%20in%202018%20after%20fabricated%20rumours%20of%20cow%20slaughter%2C%20significantly%20also%20pulled%20up%20the%20state%20police%20for%20lapses%20and%20negligence%20in%20the%20investigation%20of%20the%20case%20and%20recommended%20action%20against%20the%20concerned%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20district%20and%20sessions%20judge%20Shweta%20Dixit%20in%20her%20157-page%20judgment%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20which%20is%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20described%20the%20mob%20lynching%20of%20goat%20trader%20Qasim%20(45)%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cheinous%E2%80%9D%20crime.%20The%20behaviour%20of%20the%20mob%20in%20the%20Hapur%20case%2C%20in%20which%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinnocent%E2%80%9D%20man%20was%20murdered%2C%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwarning%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthreat%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20entire%20society%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Qasim%E2%80%99s%20brother%20Saleem%2C%20while%20talking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20he%20hopes%20that%20the%20conviction%20in%20the%20case%20would%20serve%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20example%E2%80%9D%20in%20preventing%20%E2%80%9Cacts%20of%20mob%20lynching%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20cow.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20why%20we%20requested%20the%20court%20to%20not%20hang%20them%20but%20put%20them%20in%20jail%20for%20life.%20So%20that%20they%20learn%20a%20lesson%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Saleem%2C%20who%20sells%20fruits%20from%20a%20cart%20to%20earn%20a%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20on%20March%2012%20found%20four%20points%20of%20negligence%20from%20the%20investigator%20and%20other%20police%20personnel%20involved%20in%20the%20case.%20First%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20investigating%20officer%20of%20the%20case%20did%20not%20carry%20an%20identification%20parade%20of%20the%20accused%20despite%20directions%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20the%20investigation%20of%20the%20case%20be%20supervised%20by%20a%20senior%20IPS%20officer%2C%20the%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Police%20Meerut%20Range.%20A%20survivor%20of%20the%20violent%20attack%20and%20main%20witness%2C%20Samaydeen%2C%20had%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20seeking%20an%20identification%20parade%20of%20the%20accused%20but%20despite%20the%20relief%20provided%20by%20the%20court%20in%202018%2C%20the%20investigator%20did%20not%20conduct%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20judge%20observed%20that%20a%20compact%20disc%20(CD)%20which%20showed%20one%20of%20the%20main%20accused%2C%20Rakesh%2C%20bragging%20about%20the%20crime%20in%20a%20sting%20operation%20carried%20out%20by%20television%20channel%20NDTV%2C%20was%20found%20broken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20admitted%20Rakesh%E2%80%99s%20extra-judicial%20confession%20made%20to%20the%20television%20channel%20as%20corroborative%20evidence%20to%20strengthen%20the%20prosecution%20case.%20However%2C%20Judge%20Dixit%20stated%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20objectionable%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20CD%2C%20filed%20as%20evidence%2C%20was%20not%20kept%20safe.%20The%20judge%20also%20found%20the%20police%20investigating%20officer%20guilty%20of%20negligence%20for%20not%20submitting%20a%20necessary%20certificate%20of%20a%20CD%2C%20which%20carried%20a%20video%20of%20the%20mob%20lynching%20incident%2C%20along%20with%20the%20chargesheet%20to%20make%20it%20admissible%20as%20evidence.%20Saleem%20had%20received%20the%20video%20of%20his%20brother%E2%80%99s%20lynching%20on%20his%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigator%20Laxman%20Verma%20had%20admitted%20a%20CD%20of%20the%20video%20as%20a%20witness%20exhibit%20but%20did%20not%20obtain%20the%20necessary%20certificate%20under%20Section%2065%20B%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20and%20submit%20it%20with%20the%20chargesheet%20to%20the%20make%20CB%20admissible%20as%20evidence%2C%20noted%20the%20judge.%20A%20third%20lapse%20involved%20the%20police%20not%20sending%20a%20%3Cem%3Elathi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stick)%20used%20in%20the%20crime%20and%20recovered%20from%20an%20accused%2C%20Karanpal%2C%20to%20the%20Forensic%20Science%20Laboratory%20for%20testing%20of%20blood%20and%20fingerprints.%20The%20fourth%20point%20on%20which%20the%20court%20pulled%20up%20the%20police%20was%20the%20allegation%20by%20the%20complainant%20Yasin%2C%20survivor%20Samaydeen%E2%80%99s%20brother%2C%20that%20the%20FIR%20lodged%20in%20the%20case%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20crime%20on%20June%2016%2C%202018%20under%20his%20signature%20was%20drafted%20under%20police%20pressure%20and%20was%20based%20on%20false%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Elections%20are%20Upon%20Us%20So%20the%20Shahenshah%20and%20Shah%20Regime%20Is%20Back%20to%20Playing%20Hindu%20vs%20Muslim%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Felections-are-upon-us-so-the-shahenshah-and-shah-regime-is-back-to-playing-hindu-vs-muslim%5C%22%3EElections%20are%20Upon%20Us%20So%20the%20Shahenshah%20and%20Shah%20Regime%20Is%20Back%20to%20Playing%20Hindu%20vs%20Muslim%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20initial%20FIR%20stated%20that%20the%20incident%20had%20taken%20place%20as%20a%20result%20of%20a%20motorbike%20accident%2C%20Yasin%20and%20Samaydeen%20later%20claimed%20that%20the%20FIR%20had%20been%20written%20under%20police%20pressure%20and%20stated%20that%20the%20incident%20of%20a%20motorbike%20accident%20was%20fabricated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQasim%20and%20Samaydeen%20had%20been%20brutally%20assaulted%20over%20false%20rumours%20of%20cow%20slaughter%20and%20did%20not%20suffer%20injuries%20in%20a%20motorbike%20accident%2C%20the%20victims%20said.%20This%20was%20upheld%20by%20the%20court%20in%20its%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Dixit%20said%20it%20was%20necessary%20to%20investigate%20the%20negligence%20of%20the%20police%20officers%20in%20the%20investigation%20of%20the%20case%20and%20that%20action%20be%20taken%20against%20the%20concerned%20persons.%20The%20judge%20said%20that%20a%20letter%20in%20this%20regard%20be%20written%20to%20the%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%2C%20UP%20and%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20verdict%20be%20sent%20to%20him%20for%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20six%20years%20after%20Qasim%20was%20murdered%20and%20Samaydeen%20was%20left%20grievously%20injured%20by%20the%20violent%20mob%2C%20the%20court%20on%20March%2012%20convicted%2010%20persons%20and%20sentenced%20them%20to%20life%20imprisonment.%20The%20men%20convicted%20for%20the%20crime%20were%20Yudhisthir%2C%20Rakesh%2C%20Kanu%2C%20Sonu%2C%20Mangeram%2C%20Rinku%2C%20Hariom%2C%20Manish%2C%20Lalit%20and%20Karanpal.%20An%2011th%20accused%20was%20a%20minor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQasim%20was%20among%20the%20most%20prominent%20victims%20of%20state-induced%20hate%20crimes%20in%20the%20name%20of%20cow%20slaughter%20in%20UP%20after%20the%20infamous%20Dadri%20incident%20in%202015%20when%20a%20Muslim%20man%20named%20Mohammad%20Akhlaq%20was%20beaten%20to%20death%20over%20rumours%20of%20killing%20a%20cow.%20Qasim%20was%20beaten%20to%20death%20near%20the%20fields%20of%20Bajhera%20Khurd%20village%20under%20Pilkhuwa%20police%20station%20in%20Hapur%20on%20June%2016%2C%202018.%20All%20the%20accused%20belonged%20to%20the%20Bajhera%20Khurd%20village%2C%20while%20Qasim%2C%20who%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20rural%20area%20to%20purchase%20goats%20to%20sell%20later%20in%20markets%20as%20part%20of%20his%20living%2C%20resided%20in%20Pilkhuwa%20town.%20Samaydeen%20lived%20in%20Madapur-Mustafabad%20village%2C%20close%20to%20the%20crime%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamaydeen%E2%80%99s%20testimony%2C%20as%20survivor%20and%20witness%20to%20the%20crime%2C%20proved%20to%20be%20among%20the%20clinching%20factors%20on%20which%20the%20accused%20were%20convicted%20beyond%20doubt.%20Judge%20Dixit%20convicted%20the%2010%20men%20for%20murder%2C%20attempt%20to%20murder%2C%20rioting%20with%20deadly%20weapon%20and%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20(in%20this%20case)%20and%20also%20fined%20them%20Rs%2058%2C000%20each.%20The%20court%20held%20them%20guilty%20for%20acting%20with%20a%20common%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20said%20day%20in%202018%2C%20Samaydeen%20and%20his%20neighbour%20Hasan%20were%20smoking%20bidis%20in%20their%20farm%20where%20they%20had%20gone%20to%20gather%20fodder%20for%20cattle%2C%20when%20they%20saw%20a%20mob%20chase%20Qasim%20towards%20them.%20Samaydeen%20intervened%20and%20asked%20the%20mob%20why%20were%20they%20assaulting%20Qasim.%20However%2C%20Samaydeen%20said%2C%20the%20mob%20turned%20on%20him%20as%20well%20and%20started%20hitting%20him%20with%20lathis%2C%20kicks%20and%20punches.%20In%20his%20testimony%2C%20Samaydeen%20said%20he%20was%20also%20subjected%20to%20communal%20slurs.%20Hasan%2C%20fearing%20for%20his%20life%2C%20escaped%20from%20the%20spot.%20He%20would%20later%20become%20eyewitness%20number%20two%20for%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20beating%20him%20and%20Qasim%2C%20Samaydeen%20said%20the%20members%20of%20the%20mob%20were%20shouting%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20Muslim%2C%20they%20slaughter%20cows.%20Kill%20them.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20spare%20them.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20his%20pleas%20that%20there%20were%20no%20signs%20of%20any%20cow%20being%20slaughtered%20or%20instrument%20to%20indicate%20it%2C%20fell%20on%20deaf%20ears.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20our%20head%20to%20heel%2C%20there%20was%20not%20an%20inch%20of%20the%20body%20left%20where%20they%20did%20not%20hit%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Samaydeen%2C%20who%20spent%20many%20days%20in%20two%20different%20hospitals%20recovering%20from%20a%20cracked%20head%2C%20fractures%20in%20both%20arms%20and%20a%20leg%2C%20injured%20ribs%2C%20ruptured%20ears%20and%20multiple%20abrasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQasim%2C%20who%20was%20brutally%20assaulted%2C%20was%20declared%20dead%20in%20a%20hospital.%20According%20to%20his%20post-mortem%20report%2C%20the%20cause%20of%20death%20was%20shock%20and%20haemorrhage%20as%20a%20result%20of%20multiple%20ante-mortem%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20dismissed%20the%20claim%20by%20the%20accused%20persons%20that%20Qasim%20died%20due%20to%20injuries%20suffered%20in%20a%20motorbike%20accident.%20The%20nature%20of%20his%20injuries%2C%20which%20included%20multiple%20contusions%20on%20the%20back%20and%20abdomen%2C%20lacerated%20wounds%20including%20one%20on%20the%20leg%20that%20was%20bone%20deep%2C%20broken%20bones%20in%20hand%20and%20forearm%20and%20injuries%20to%20the%20head%2C%20proved%20that%20he%20did%20not%20die%20of%20an%20accident%2C%20said%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Don't%20Hide%20Your%20Communal%20Prejudice%20Under%20the%20Cloak%20of%20Protecting%20Our%20Roads%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fdont-hide-your-communal-prejudice-under-the-cloak-of-protecting-our-roads%5C%22%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20Hide%20Your%20Communal%20Prejudice%20Under%20the%20Cloak%20of%20Protecting%20Our%20Roads%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20judge%20noted%20that%20during%20the%20entire%20investigation%2C%20there%20was%20no%20mention%20of%20a%20motorcycle%20owner%20or%20number%20plate%20of%20the%20alleged%20motorcycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20victim%20side%20had%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20investigation%20in%20the%20case%20from%20the%20very%20beginning.%20It%20was%20only%20after%20they%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20on%20its%20directions%20Yasin%E2%80%99s%20statement%2C%20in%20which%20he%20said%20that%20his%20initial%20complaint%20was%20written%20under%20police%20pressure%2C%20was%20recorded%20in%20August%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20had%20brought%20widespread%20condemnation%20for%20the%20state%20police%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20crime%20itself%20when%20three%20policemen%20were%20photographed%20leading%20a%20mob%20as%20it%20dragged%20away%20the%20bloodied%20body%20of%20Qasim%2C%20probably%20still%20alive%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20violence.%20The%20police%20issued%20an%20apology%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20its%20personnel%20%E2%80%93%20an%20inspector%20and%20two%20constables%20%E2%80%93%20but%20clarified%20that%20Qasim%20was%20dragged%20on%20the%20ground%20%E2%80%9Cbecause%20of%20the%20non-availability%20of%20an%20ambulance%20at%20that%20moment%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20he%20was%20later%20rushed%20to%20a%20hospital%20in%20an%20emergency%20van.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20families%20of%20Samaydeen%20and%20Qasim%20are%20happy%20with%20the%20conviction%20and%20said%20justice%20was%20done%2C%20they%20also%20acknowledged%20the%20difficulties%20the%20traumatic%20incident%20and%20the%20long%20legal%20battle%20brought%20with%20them.%20Yasin%2C%20a%20daily-wage%20labourer%2C%20says%20it%20was%20tough%20to%20leave%20aside%20his%20work%20and%20attend%20court%20hearings.%20He%20claims%20the%20family%20was%20forced%20to%20sell%20200-300%20yards%20of%20land%20to%20sustain%20the%20arduous%20legal%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaleem%2C%20Qasim%E2%80%99s%20brother%2C%20said%20that%20for%20almost%20six%20years%20the%20family%20was%20focused%20on%20securing%20justice%20even%20as%20they%20tried%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20displayed%20patience.%20We%20had%20faith%20in%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20443px)%2085vw%2C%20443px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14094107%2FPSX_20240314_035446.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14094107%2FPSX_20240314_035446.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14094107%2FPSX_20240314_035446-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14094107%2FPSX_20240314_035446-768x1024.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701551%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22591%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESaleem.%20Photo%3A%20Omar%20Rashid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Qasim%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20it%20was%20Saleem%20who%20had%20to%20take%20care%20of%20his%20elder%20brother%E2%80%99s%20children%20along%20with%20his%20own%20family.%20While%20he%20is%20grateful%20to%20the%20team%20of%20lawyers%20led%20by%20Vrinda%20Grover%20who%20fought%20the%20case%20at%20all%20levels%2C%20he%20feels%20he%20still%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20fear%20as%20the%20kin%20of%20the%20convicted%20men%20may%20be%20gunning%20for%20revenge.%20This%2C%20despite%20him%20having%20a%20police%20guard%20for%20security%20provided%20by%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicted%20men%20belong%20to%20a%20dominant%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20question%20lingers%20though%2C%20if%20the%20rumours%20of%20cow%20slaughter%20and%20motorbike%20accident%20were%20both%20fake%2C%20why%20did%20the%20mob%20target%20Qasim%20and%20Samaydeen%3F%20Saleem%20says%20the%20accused%20persons%20would%20know%20best%20but%20feels%20the%20incident%20may%20have%20been%20motivated%20by%20the%20emergence%20of%20violent%20vigilantism%20in%20the%20state%20after%20the%20BJP%20came%20to%20power.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20cow%20slaughter%20rumours%20were%20fake.%20Mob%20lynching%20had%20become%20a%20trend%20then%20(in%202018).%20It%20was%20all%20about%20making%20it%20Hindu-Muslim%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Saleem.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710389889000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F23102651%2Fhapur_twitter1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fhapur-mob-lynching-conviction-court-finds-up-police-guilty-of-negligence-in-investigation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Victim%20Qasim%E2%80%99s%20brother%20Saleem%20said%20he%20hopes%20that%20the%20conviction%20in%20the%20case%20would%20serve%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20example%E2%80%9D%20in%20preventing%20%E2%80%9Cacts%20of%20mob%20lynching%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20cow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fhapur-mob-lynching-conviction-court-finds-up-police-guilty-of-negligence-in-investigation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BBig%20Controversy%26quot%3B%3A%20South%20Africa%20Great's%20Honest%20Take%20On%20MI%20Captaincy%20Change%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20upcoming%20Indian%20Premier%20League%20season%2C%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Hardik%20Pandya%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F64177-hardik-himanshu-pandya-playerprofile%5C%22%3EHardik%20Pandya%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20will%20be%20leading%20five-time%20champions%20Mumbai%20Indians.%20In%20December%20last%20year%2C%20MI%20traded%20Hardik%20in%20an%20all-cash%20deal%20from%20Gujarat%20Titans%20and%20later%20named%20him%20the%20skipper.%20Rohit%2C%20who%20led%20MI%20to%20five%20titles%20in%202013%2C%202015%2C%202017%2C%202019%20and%202020%2C%20will%20be%20there%20in%20the%20team%20but%20no%20more%20the%20captain.%20Speaking%20on%20the%20surprise%20change%20made%20by%20Mumbai%2C%20South%20Africa%20great%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22AB%20de%20Villiers%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F699-ab-de-villiers-playerprofile%5C%22%3EAB%20de%20Villiers%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20it%20created%20%26quot%3Bbig%20controversy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMumbai%20Indians%2C%20incredibly%20successful%20team%20of%20the%20IPL.%20They%20have%20won%2