fee-for-select-users-124031301013_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fquick-commerce-major-zepto-introduces-rs-2-platform-fee-for-select-users-124031301013_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Interim%20Stay%20on%20Union%20Government%20Notifying%20Its%20Fact-Checking%20Unit%2C%20Says%20Bombay%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F02120845%2F2155086006_de9f5d98ef_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20will%20be%20no%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20notifying%20a%20fact-checking%20unit%20(FCU)%20as%20per%20its%20amended%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20rules%2C%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20(March%2013).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20more%20than%20a%20month%20after%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbombay-hc-split-verdict-petition-it-amendment-rules%5C%22%3Edelivered%20a%20split%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20specific%20rule%20dealing%20with%20the%20FCU%20and%20two%20days%20after%20a%20tie-breaker%20judge%20said%20there%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmaharashtra%2Fbombay-hc-refuses-to-grant-interim-stay-on-setting-up-fact-checking-unit-to-identify-fake-news-against-govt-2931452%5C%22%3Eno%20case%20for%20stopping%20the%20government%20from%20notifying%20an%20FCU%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20third%20judge%20has%20rendered%20his%20opinion.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20majority%20view%20is%20that%20the%20interim%20applications%20for%20stay%20and%20continuation%20of%20the%20previous%20statement%20(by%20the%20Union%20%5Bgovernment%5D%20not%20to%20notify%20the%20FCU)%20are%20rejected%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Ffact-check-unit-bombay-high-court-central-govt-it-rules-amendment-2023-social-media-content-252162%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20reconstituted%20two-judge%20bench%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20split%20verdict%20on%20January%2031%2C%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%2C%20among%20whom%20is%20comedian%20Kunal%20Kamra%2C%20sought%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20FCU%20being%20notified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Ffiles%2FInformation%2520Technology%2520%2528Intermediary%2520Guidelines%2520and%2520Digital%2520Media%2520Ethics%2520Code%2529%2520Rules%252C%25202021%2520%2528updated%252006.04.2023%2529-.pdf%5C%22%3ERule%203(1)(b)(v)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20amended%20rule%20that%20the%20petitioners%20have%20challenged%2C%20says%20that%20an%20FCU%20can%20identify%20content%20online%20relating%20to%20%E2%80%9Cany%20business%20of%20the%20central%20%5BUnion%5D%20government%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfake%2C%20false%20or%20misleading%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20FCU%20makes%20such%20an%20identification%2C%20social%20media%20platforms%20like%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%20would%20either%20have%20to%20take%20down%20the%20content%20in%20question%20or%20add%20a%20disclaimer%20mentioning%20the%20FCU%E2%80%99s%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20split%20verdict%20made%20in%20January%2C%20Justice%20Gautam%20Patel%20said%20that%20rule%203(1)(b)(v)%20must%20be%20struck%20down%20but%20Justice%20Neela%20Gokhale%20upheld%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20referred%20the%20matter%20to%20a%20third%20judge%2C%20Justice%20A.S.%20Chandurkar%2C%20for%20a%20decision%20in%20order%20to%20resolve%20the%20impasse.%20He%20was%20also%20meant%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20petitions%20seeking%20an%20interim%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandurkar%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20decided%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20rule%20in%20question%20but%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011)%2C%20he%20said%20regarding%20the%20interim%20petition%20that%20there%20was%20no%20case%20for%20the%20government%20to%20be%20stopped%20from%20notifying%20an%20FCU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20no%20case%20is%20made%20out%20to%20direct%20the%20respondent%20(Centre)%20%5Bthe%20Union%20government%5D%20to%20continue%20its%20statement%20that%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%20would%20not%20be%20notified%20pending%20proceedings%20on%20the%20petitions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%20the%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20said%20the%20FCU%20will%20not%20seek%20to%20censor%20political%20opinions%2C%20satire%20or%20comedy%20and%20that%20the%20FCU%E2%80%99s%20actions%20will%20still%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20final%20decision%20on%20the%20rule%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbalance%20of%20convenience%20tilts%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20non-applicants%20%5Bthe%20Union%20government%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freepressjournal.in%2Fmumbai%2Fbombay-hc-refuses-interim-stay-on-fact-checking-unit-notification-under-amended-it-rules%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%20according%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFree%20Press%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20say%20the%20amended%20IT%20rules%20will%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20unilaterally%20and%20arbitrarily%20take%20decisions%20what%20is%20or%20isn%E2%80%99t%20true%20and%20pose%20a%20danger%20to%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20had%20earlier%20said%20it%20would%20not%20notify%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%20until%20the%20high%20court%20took%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20rule%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20said%20after%20the%20split%20verdict%20that%20this%20assurance%20would%20continue%20only%20until%20the%20court%20took%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20interim%20stay%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710344536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F02120845%2F2155086006_de9f5d98ef_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-interim-stay-notification-fact-checking-unit-bombay-hc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20high%20court%20said%20that%20given%20the%20government's%20assurances%20and%20that%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20relevant%20Information%20Technology%20rule%20is%20still%20pending%20in%20court%2C%20there%20was%20no%20reason%20to%20stop%20the%20government%20from%20notifying%20a%20fact-checking%20unit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-interim-stay-notification-fact-checking-unit-bombay-hc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BToday%20is%20a%20special%20day%20for%20the%20Tata%20Group...%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Tata%20Sons%20Chairman%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710344177000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108471238%2Cimgsize-1475890.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Ftoday-is-a-special-day-for-the-tata-group-says-tata-sons-chairman-n-chandrasekaran%2Farticleshow%2F108471245.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20three%20chip%20plants%20by%20Tata%20Electronics%20and%20CG%20Power%2C%20with%20a%20total%20investment%20of%20Rs%201.26%20lakh%20crore.%20The%20plants%20include%20the%20country's%20first%20high-tech%20chip%20manufacturing%20plant%20of%20Tata%20Electronics%20in%20Dholera's%20special%20industrial%20region%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20along%20with%20an%20assembly%20and%20test%20facility%20in%20Jagiroad%2C%20Assam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22ca